events.title: U.S. President John F. Kennedy assassinated
events.description: The most notorious political murder in recent American history occurred this day in 1963, when John F. Kennedy, the 35th U.S. president(1961–63), was shot and killed in Dallas, Texas, while riding in an open car

events.title: Angela Merkel becomes first female German Chancellor
events.description: German politician Angela Merkel was sworn in as the country's chancellor, becoming the first woman to hold the post

events.title: Pixar Releases Groundbreaking Toy Story
events.description: Pixar's Toy Story, the first entirely computer-animated feature-length film, was released in 1995 and became a critical and commercial hit, revolutionizing the animation industry.

events.title: Mount Merapi eruption on Java island kills 64
events.description: Mount Merapi, on the island of Java, erupted, killing 64 people

events.title: Margaret Thatcher resigns as British Prime Minister
events.description: Margaret Thatcher announced her resignation as British prime minister after a split occurred in the ranks of the Conservative Party

events.title: Mike Tyson Becomes Youngest Heavyweight Champion
events.description: With a second-round knockout of Trevor Berbick, 20-year-old Mike Tyson became the youngest heavyweight champion in boxing history.

events.title: Juan Carlos Becomes King of Spain After Franco's Death
events.description: Juan Carlos became king of Spain, two days after the death of Francisco Franco

events.title: Lebanon Proclaims Independence from France in 1943
events.description: Lebanon proclaimed its independence from France in 1943, but did not achieve full independence until 1946.

events.title: Birth of Victorian Novelist George Eliot
events.description: Victorian English novelist George Eliot, who developed the method of psychological analysis characteristic of modern fiction and was known for such works as Middlemarch (1871–72)—was born.

events.title: Blackbeard the Pirate Killed Off North Carolina Coast in 1718
events.description: The infamous pirate Blackbeard, whose real name was Edward Teach, was killed in a battle off the coast of North Carolina in 1718. He was a notorious figure who terrorized the Atlantic coast, but was ultimately defeated by British naval forces.
